    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Archaeological industry dated to about 8000 BCE, characterized by a sudden technological change evinced by grinding stones, more bone tools, polished bone artifacts, decorated ostrich eggshell, and shell beads. This change is believed to coincide with climactic shift toward higher temperatures.</Note_Text>
